{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "First, we adopt an actor-centric view of digital transformation, as opposed to the more common technology-centered one (Nadkarmi and Prügl 2021;den Hond and Moser 2023).",
    "Next, we carry out an explicit ethical analysis based on contemporary virtue ethics tradition (Vallor 2016; Hagendorff 2022), acknowledging principles mainly from neo-Aristotelianism (Snow 2017), Catholic social teaching (CST) (Congregation for the Doctrine of the Faith 1986, 72), and the works of Alasdair MacIntyre ([1981] 2007, 1988, 1990).",
    "Although we use elements from sociology (Rodríguez-Lluesma et al. 2021), social psychology, organizational behavior (Trenerry et al.",
    "2021), economics (Frey and Osborne 2017; Bowles 2014; Mokyr et al. 2015; Arntz et al.",
    "2016 Arntz et al., 2017; Nedelkoska and Quintini 2018; Acemoglu andRestrepo 2018, 2020), and information and communications technology (ICT) systems (Verhoef et al. 2021), they do not constitute our main vantage point."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Next, we carry out an explicit ethical analysis based on contemporary virtue ethics tradition (Vallor 2016; Hagendorff 2022), acknowledging principles mainly from neo-Aristotelianism (Snow 2017), Catholic social teaching (CST) (Congregation for the Doctrine of the Faith 1986, 72), and the works of Alasdair MacIntyre ([1981] 2007, 1988, 1990)."
  ]
}